title: Mauritius  CPI Housing Utilities
description: CPI Housing Utilities in Mauritius increased to 98.88 points in October from 95.47 points in September of 2022. CPI Housing Utilities in Mauritius averaged 97.33 points from 2013 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 101.72 points in April of 2015 and a record low of 87.61 points in April of 2021. This page provides - Mauritius  Cpi Housing Utilities- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Central Statistics Office, Mauritius
